

Radium V0.66.0
Released 2012-08-05


HOW TO MAKE IT RUN

make packages
make
./start.sh



INTRODUCTION
        Radium is a free (as in speech) music editor with a novel interface.
        It's inspired by trackers, but has fewer limitations and uses graphics to show musical data. 


BUILD DEPENDENCIES FEDORA:
        qt3-devel
        libXaw-devel
        ncurses-devel
        python2-devel
        alsa-lib-devel
        jack-audio-connection-kit-devel
        PyQt4
        gtk2-devel


BUILD DEPENDENCIES UBUNTU: (might be incomplete)
      libxaw7-dev
      ncurses-dev
      libjack-jackd2-dev
      python-dev
      libqt3-mt-dev
      qt3-dev-tools
      libasound-dev
      python-qt4

